{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/punc/punc-01046/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PUNC-01046"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:10:46"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Punch-Drunk Love"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Vertical stripes of shades of pink and blue."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PUNC-01046","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PUNC-01046"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1/b7610bc6-8e81-4b6f-8d21-77d2073fda54","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-14T19:39:02.114Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This interstitial image mirrors <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" class=\"text-blue-500 underline hover:text-blue-600\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/punc-01009.html\">the one that, just seconds ago, only contains red and orange hues</a>. Following a shot that resembles a blue night sky with stars, it mixes reds (Lena) and blues (Barry) to foreshadow the film's central coupling.</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1#xywh=25,169,1877,287"},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1/af8fb1c1-c54f-4691-a9d6-61edec144028","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-14T19:39:28.065Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Brian Price writes of the early appearance of this color field and how it defies viewers' expectations of narrative: “This juxtaposition of abstraction and narrative comes early in the film and announces a tension in Anderson's aesthetic between storytelling and abstract visual expression. We might also understand abstraction here as a moment of respite from the banal space of the warehouse; an intrusion of beauty in an otherwise lusterless environment” (Price, \"Color,\" 24).</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1#xywh=1139,517,247,343"},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1/7e97a5cb-b9f7-4174-b4ab-53975ea91231","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-14T19:40:02.697Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>PTA has spoken of his dream of making a film without dialogue, only image and sound. \"Blossoms &amp; Blood,\" a short film included on the film's DVD release, is one result of this desire (Xixax TV, \"<i>Punch-Drunk Love</i> - Paul Thomas Anderson interviewed by Elvis Mitchell on KCRW's <i>The Treatment</i>\").</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01046/canvas/1#xywh=660,516,247,346"}]}]}]}
